translate ru strings:

    old "Sarah woke early next morning to the sounds of heavy boots scraping against the gravel of the road."
    new "Sarah woke early next morning to the sounds of heavy boots scraping against the gravel of the road."

    old "Time to wake up. We need to make good time."
    new "Time to wake up. We need to make good time."

    old "Sarah slowly opened her eyes to see all the others were already moving about, busily preparing the wagon for departure."
    new "Sarah slowly opened her eyes to see all the others were already moving about, busily preparing the wagon for departure."

    old "Part of her was annoyed that they had let her sleep out at all."
    new "Part of her was annoyed that they had let her sleep out at all."

    old "Sigmund."
    new "Sigmund."

    old "I want to help."
    new "I want to help."

    old "I know, Sarah. We talked about what you can do."
    new "I know, Sarah. We talked about what you can do."

    old "I know...but I mean, I don't want to feel like I'm holding you all back."
    new "I know...but I mean, I don't want to feel like I'm holding you all back."

    old "You can wake me up, same time as the others. I can carry boxes, I can help rig the cart...you just need to give me a chance."
    new "You can wake me up, same time as the others. I can carry boxes, I can help rig the cart...you just need to give me a chance."

    old "For a moment, Sigmund was silent and observed her."
    new "For a moment, Sigmund was silent and observed her."

    old "Sure, Sarah. I promise I'll treat you like the others."
    new "Sure, Sarah. I promise I'll treat you like the others."

    old "Thank you. That's all I want."
    new "Thank you. That's all I want."

    old "Sigmund kicked the side of a crate."
    new "Sigmund kicked the side of a crate."

    old "Start by loading that onto the wagon."
    new "Start by loading that onto the wagon."

    old "Eager to prove herself, Sarah crawled out of her bedroll and grabbed the crate."
    new "Eager to prove herself, Sarah crawled out of her bedroll and grabbed the crate."

    old "As she rose to lift it, she nearly felt her legs give out from under her."
    new "As she rose to lift it, she nearly felt her legs give out from under her."

    old "Sigmund was looking at her, a small grin on his face."
    new "Sigmund was looking at her, a small grin on his face."

    old "No...none...at all..."
    new "No...none...at all..."

    old "Sarah tried to speak through gritted teeth as she forced herself to carry the heavy box to the back of the cart."
    new "Sarah tried to speak through gritted teeth as she forced herself to carry the heavy box to the back of the cart."

    old "It took her all of her strength to lift the crate up and drop it onto the cargo section of the wagon."
    new "It took her all of her strength to lift the crate up and drop it onto the cargo section of the wagon."

    old "Looking around her at how busy the others were, Sarah wanted to hate herself for her weakness."
    new "Looking around her at how busy the others were, Sarah wanted to hate herself for her weakness."

    old "All her life she had been raised for a very singular task, and none of that involved any need for physical strength."
    new "All her life she had been raised for a very singular task, and none of that involved any need for physical strength."

    old "But out here, all her history lessons and dancing classes weren't worth a single thing."
    new "But out here, all her history lessons and dancing classes weren't worth a single thing."

    old "Still, Sarah forced herself to be useful, if only not to lose face in front of Sigmund who she had just earlier begged for a chance."
    new "Still, Sarah forced herself to be useful, if only not to lose face in front of Sigmund who she had just earlier begged for a chance."

    old "It was still early in the morning when they were ready to depart."
    new "It was still early in the morning when they were ready to depart."

    old "As per usual, Sarah took her position near the front on the box with Sigmund, while the others rode in the back."
    new "As per usual, Sarah took her position near the front on the box with Sigmund, while the others rode in the back."

    old "As the horses began pulling the cart forward, it quickly made its way up the road."
    new "As the horses began pulling the cart forward, it quickly made its way up the road."

    old "It wasn't long before the forest that Sarah had so far seen only from a distance, was all around them."
    new "It wasn't long before the forest that Sarah had so far seen only from a distance, was all around them."

    old "As they drew deeper into the forest, even the light failed to pierce through the thick canopy above."
    new "As they drew deeper into the forest, even the light failed to pierce through the thick canopy above."

    old "The foliage above dimmed the light that did pass, causing the whole world to be covered in a shadow."
    new "The foliage above dimmed the light that did pass, causing the whole world to be covered in a shadow."

    old "Sarah looked off to her sides."
    new "Sarah looked off to her sides."

    old "Where at first the trees were sparse, the quickly grew thicker and thicker."
    new "Where at first the trees were sparse, the quickly grew thicker and thicker."

    old "Before long, Sarah could barely look out in each direction for more than a few feet."
    new "Before long, Sarah could barely look out in each direction for more than a few feet."

    old "The most discomforting thing were the sounds."
    new "The most discomforting thing were the sounds."

    old "The forest was full of them."
    new "The forest was full of them."

    old "Any and all kinds, familir and unfamiliar, she tried to make sense of all the things she heard."
    new "Any and all kinds, familir and unfamiliar, she tried to make sense of all the things she heard."

    old "At first she feared every new and strange sound, but she kept looking to Sigmund."
    new "At first she feared every new and strange sound, but she kept looking to Sigmund."

    old "Sigmund sat firm and stern, his eyes fixed on the road."
    new "Sigmund sat firm and stern, his eyes fixed on the road."

    old "So long as he isn't afraid, there would be no reason for her to be, so thought Sarah."
    new "So long as he isn't afraid, there would be no reason for her to be, so thought Sarah."

    old "Where before she had been able to have an easy banter with Sigmund, he seemed now more distant."
    new "Where before she had been able to have an easy banter with Sigmund, he seemed now more distant."

    old "More focussed."
    new "More focussed."

    old "In that silence, they rode for hours, the twisting and bending road appearing and dissapearing behind thick forest."
    new "In that silence, they rode for hours, the twisting and bending road appearing and dissapearing behind thick forest."

    old "The shadow that had fallen over the world was quickly dimming further."
    new "The shadow that had fallen over the world was quickly dimming further."

    old "Sarah worried about the idea of sleeping in this place."
    new "Sarah worried about the idea of sleeping in this place."

    old "It shouldn't have felt any different from sleeping out on the field, and yet Sarah couldn't help but feel different about it."
    new "It shouldn't have felt any different from sleeping out on the field, and yet Sarah couldn't help but feel different about it."

    old "Something about the place made her uneasy."
    new "Something about the place made her uneasy."

    old "Then, she saw Sigmund's hand move quickly."
    new "Then, she saw Sigmund's hand move quickly."

    old "He gripped the handle of his sword with one hand."
    new "He gripped the handle of his sword with one hand."

    old "Sarah said nothing, but could see in his posture that he was on edge."
    new "Sarah said nothing, but could see in his posture that he was on edge."

    old "Movement in the trees."
    new "Movement in the trees."

    old "Sarah looked ahead."
    new "Sarah looked ahead."

    old "Suddenly, emerging from the underbrush on the side of the road, two men stepped out onto the road."
    new "Suddenly, emerging from the underbrush on the side of the road, two men stepped out onto the road."

    old "They blocked their path."
    new "They blocked their path."

    old "Sarah could see their faces were covered up. Their hands resting casually, yet obviously, on a pair of daggers on their hips."
    new "Sarah could see their faces were covered up. Their hands resting casually, yet obviously, on a pair of daggers on their hips."

    old "She didn't need to know much of the world to know these people were bad news."
    new "She didn't need to know much of the world to know these people were bad news."

    old "As the cart slowed down, there was an uneasy silence."
    new "As the cart slowed down, there was an uneasy silence."

    old "Neither Sigmund, nor the robbers spoke, for a moment."
    new "Neither Sigmund, nor the robbers spoke, for a moment."

    old "We're not looking for trouble."
    new "We're not looking for trouble."

    old "Robber\" \"Well, you found it anyway."
    new "Robber\" \"Well, you found it anyway."

    old "You step off aside, we'll be on our way and nobody needs to get hurt."
    new "You step off aside, we'll be on our way and nobody needs to get hurt."

    old "The other robber laughed."
    new "The other robber laughed."

    old "Robber\" \"That's one way of resolving this. How about I tell you my way, grandpa?"
    new "Robber\" \"That's one way of resolving this. How about I tell you my way, grandpa?"

    old "Robber\" \"You're gonna get off that cart, me and my friend over here are gonna take your daughter or whatever she is to you, and take good care of her."
    new "Robber\" \"You're gonna get off that cart, me and my friend over here are gonna take your daughter or whatever she is to you, and take good care of her."

    old "Robber\" \"As for you, I'll promise I'll try and make it as painless as I can make it."
    new "Robber\" \"As for you, I'll promise I'll try and make it as painless as I can make it."

    old "She had been warned a great many times by now about the dangers of the old road, but it was different to experience it."
    new "She had been warned a great many times by now about the dangers of the old road, but it was different to experience it."

    old "She looked at Sigmund, whose face remained unchanged."
    new "She looked at Sigmund, whose face remained unchanged."

    old "Last offer boys."
    new "Last offer boys."

    old "Fuck off back into the forest, or we'll do this the other way."
    new "Fuck off back into the forest, or we'll do this the other way."

    old "One of the robbers stepped forward."
    new "One of the robbers stepped forward."

    old "Robber\" \"Guess it's gonna be the other way."
    new "Robber\" \"Guess it's gonna be the other way."

    old "Sigmund leapt off from the box, landing off to the side."
    new "Sigmund leapt off from the box, landing off to the side."

    old "As he walked around to the front, Sarah could see he was carrying his large two-handed broad sword."
    new "As he walked around to the front, Sarah could see he was carrying his large two-handed broad sword."

    old "Sigmund placed one leg forward, another back."
    new "Sigmund placed one leg forward, another back."

    old "Bending down his knees, Sarah watched him move into a stance."
    new "Bending down his knees, Sarah watched him move into a stance."

    old "His shoulders seemed to widen, bulge, as he drew his blade out from its sheath."
    new "His shoulders seemed to widen, bulge, as he drew his blade out from its sheath."

    old "It glimmered, even in the shade."
    new "It glimmered, even in the shade."

    old "It was the first thing she noticed, how his blade was clean and maintained, their daggers stained in rust. It said everything."
    new "It was the first thing she noticed, how his blade was clean and maintained, their daggers stained in rust. It said everything."

    old "For a moment, she thought she could see regret in the eyes of the two robbers."
    new "For a moment, she thought she could see regret in the eyes of the two robbers."

    old "The kind of realization that you could see in people, only when they were too deep into a mistake they could no longer get out of."
    new "The kind of realization that you could see in people, only when they were too deep into a mistake they could no longer get out of."

    old "The two robbers held up their daggers and began to circle Sigmund, each taking one side."
    new "The two robbers held up their daggers and began to circle Sigmund, each taking one side."

    old "Sigmund only kept his stance, his sword raised."
    new "Sigmund only kept his stance, his sword raised."

    old "Then he moved."
    new "Then he moved."

    old "Sarah had expected Sigmund to be strong, his body told as much despite his age, but she was stunned to see his speed."
    new "Sarah had expected Sigmund to be strong, his body told as much despite his age, but she was stunned to see his speed."

    old "He had closed the distance between himself and the first robber before he had even been able to raise up his weapons."
    new "He had closed the distance between himself and the first robber before he had even been able to raise up his weapons."

    old "Sigmund's blade fell down and caught the man in the neck, the blood spewed out of him, cast like a red mist to the forest air."
    new "Sigmund's blade fell down and caught the man in the neck, the blood spewed out of him, cast like a red mist to the forest air."

    old "The other tried to rush Sigmund from behind, hoping to take him by surprise."
    new "The other tried to rush Sigmund from behind, hoping to take him by surprise."

    old "But Sarah watched as Sigmund pulled his blade free from the man's neck, spun around, diving low, and catching the other robber above his upper leg."
    new "But Sarah watched as Sigmund pulled his blade free from the man's neck, spun around, diving low, and catching the other robber above his upper leg."

    old "The blade went clean through and the second robber stumbled, falling as he failed too late that his leg was gone."
    new "The blade went clean through and the second robber stumbled, falling as he failed too late that his leg was gone."

    old "Sarah only now realized she had not been breathing the entire time."
    new "Sarah only now realized she had not been breathing the entire time."

    old "She could hear the muted screams from the robber that had lost his leg, but not yet his life."
    new "She could hear the muted screams from the robber that had lost his leg, but not yet his life."

    old "In front of the horses, she could see him crawl along the dirty road."
    new "In front of the horses, she could see him crawl along the dirty road."

    old "A wound like that would have likely been fatal even if they had been in a city hospital, but out here, there was no way he would live."
    new "A wound like that would have likely been fatal even if they had been in a city hospital, but out here, there was no way he would live."

    old "She looked on as Sigmund slowly walked up to the second robber."
    new "She looked on as Sigmund slowly walked up to the second robber."

    old "He brought his sword high and brought it down, driving the tip of his blade through the man's neck."
    new "He brought his sword high and brought it down, driving the tip of his blade through the man's neck."

    old "The second robber's body slumped instantly, like a puppet whose strings were cut."
    new "The second robber's body slumped instantly, like a puppet whose strings were cut."

    old "Sarah spun around as she heard more sounds from the side of the cart."
    new "Sarah spun around as she heard more sounds from the side of the cart."

    old "But it was only Sakar and Krip."
    new "But it was only Sakar and Krip."

    old "You already took care of them?"
    new "You already took care of them?"

    old "Sigmund had pushed the robber's bodies off the side of the road and walked back up to the cart."
    new "Sigmund had pushed the robber's bodies off the side of the road and walked back up to the cart."

    old "Just two idiots."
    new "Just two idiots."

    old "Not even worth the effort to call for help."
    new "Not even worth the effort to call for help."

    old "Sakar sighed."
    new "Sakar sighed."

    old "You know, Krip and me are out back there, bored out of our mind."
    new "You know, Krip and me are out back there, bored out of our mind."

    old "Least you could have done was let us have this one."
    new "Least you could have done was let us have this one."

    old "Sigmund shrugged as he climbed back onto the cart."
    new "Sigmund shrugged as he climbed back onto the cart."

    old "You can have the next one."
    new "You can have the next one."

    old "Fine, old man, I'm gonna keep you to that."
    new "Fine, old man, I'm gonna keep you to that."

    old "Sakar and Krip dissapeared into the back of the cart."
    new "Sakar and Krip dissapeared into the back of the cart."

    old "Sigmund grabbed the reins again and snapped them, forcing the horses back into motion."
    new "Sigmund grabbed the reins again and snapped them, forcing the horses back into motion."

    old "Sarah felt the cart begin to move and slowly the two bodies dissapeared behind them."
    new "Sarah felt the cart begin to move and slowly the two bodies dissapeared behind them."

    old "She turned to Sigmund."
    new "She turned to Sigmund."

    old "You...you weren't afraid?"
    new "You...you weren't afraid?"

    old "If they had been serious, maybe."
    new "If they had been serious, maybe."

    old "But those were idiots. Too stupid to realize what or who they were dealing with."
    new "But those were idiots. Too stupid to realize what or who they were dealing with."

    old "He pulled on the reins, guiding the horses around another bend in the road."
    new "He pulled on the reins, guiding the horses around another bend in the road."

    old "Out here you got all types, Sarah."
    new "Out here you got all types, Sarah."

    old "You got real mean bastards, but you also got the morons like those two."
    new "You got real mean bastards, but you also got the morons like those two."

    old "Sarah felt uneasy at how untroubled Sigmund seemed to be at having just killed two men."
    new "Sarah felt uneasy at how untroubled Sigmund seemed to be at having just killed two men."

    old "Don't you feel bad about killing them?"
    new "Don't you feel bad about killing them?"

    old "Sigmund looked at her as he continued to guide the horses along."
    new "Sigmund looked at her as he continued to guide the horses along."

    old "Look at me, Sarah."
    new "Look at me, Sarah."

    old "She did."
    new "She did."

    old "Those two sons-of-bitches would not have thought twice about dragging you into the forest and raping you."
    new "Those two sons-of-bitches would not have thought twice about dragging you into the forest and raping you."

    old "You go around feeling sorry for people out here, you're the one whose gonna end up being sorry."
    new "You go around feeling sorry for people out here, you're the one whose gonna end up being sorry."

    old "This isn't like where you're from."
    new "This isn't like where you're from."

    old "People will use whatever they can to get one over on you."
    new "People will use whatever they can to get one over on you."

    old "They'll use force if they can, if not, they play on your emotions."
    new "They'll use force if they can, if not, they play on your emotions."

    old "You give them any sign of weakness, they pounce on it. You understand me?"
    new "You give them any sign of weakness, they pounce on it. You understand me?"

    old "She knew he was right, and still she felt uneasy."
    new "She knew he was right, and still she felt uneasy."

    old "It was hard for her to have lived an entire life, safe and secure, to now suddenly see danger in every direction."
    new "It was hard for her to have lived an entire life, safe and secure, to now suddenly see danger in every direction."

    old "Still, she was glad she had Sigmund and the others."
    new "Still, she was glad she had Sigmund and the others."

    old "They had been right. She wouldn't have survived for a day out here without them."
    new "They had been right. She wouldn't have survived for a day out here without them."

    old "Despite the slaying of the two bandits, Sarah found the rest of the day to be rather uneventful."
    new "Despite the slaying of the two bandits, Sarah found the rest of the day to be rather uneventful."

    old "Once they were deep into the forest, everything ended up looking like everywhere else."
    new "Once they were deep into the forest, everything ended up looking like everywhere else."

    old "Time, much like their surroundings, seemed to slide past unnoticed and unremembered."
    new "Time, much like their surroundings, seemed to slide past unnoticed and unremembered."

    old "They had made camp deep in the forest."
    new "They had made camp deep in the forest."

    old "Sigmund had told her that they'd likely be another day or two before they would even break past the main body of the forest."
    new "Sigmund had told her that they'd likely be another day or two before they would even break past the main body of the forest."

    old "Sarah tried to wrap her head around it."
    new "Sarah tried to wrap her head around it."

    old "Rosanna had stretches of nature as well, but nothing like this."
    new "Rosanna had stretches of nature as well, but nothing like this."

    old "This part of the world, with little remaining civilization, could offer no resistance to the march of nature."
    new "This part of the world, with little remaining civilization, could offer no resistance to the march of nature."

    old "The meal Sarah prepared for the group seemed to be approved."
    new "The meal Sarah prepared for the group seemed to be approved."

    old "She felt as though with each meal, her cooking was improving. She hoped the others thought likewise."
    new "She felt as though with each meal, her cooking was improving. She hoped the others thought likewise."

    old "After their meal was finished, Sigmund and Krip walked away from the camp, discussing something that Sarah could no longer overhear."
    new "After their meal was finished, Sigmund and Krip walked away from the camp, discussing something that Sarah could no longer overhear."

    old "She called it discussing, but the truth was Krip said little back, and it was more of a monologue that Sigmund seemed to be having with himself."
    new "She called it discussing, but the truth was Krip said little back, and it was more of a monologue that Sigmund seemed to be having with himself."

    old "Looking out across the fire, Sarah could see Sakar looking back at her."
    new "Looking out across the fire, Sarah could see Sakar looking back at her."

    old "Your cooking is improving."
    new "Your cooking is improving."

    old "Out of all the things she had expected from him, a compliment wasn't one of them."
    new "Out of all the things she had expected from him, a compliment wasn't one of them."

    old "She couldn't surpress a smile."
    new "She couldn't surpress a smile."

    old "I'm trying my best, but it's not as easy as I first thought."
    new "I'm trying my best, but it's not as easy as I first thought."

    old "I'm used to Sigmund or Krip cooking."
    new "I'm used to Sigmund or Krip cooking."

    old "Be thankful you haven't been subjected to any of that yet."
    new "Be thankful you haven't been subjected to any of that yet."

    old "Sakar stood up."
    new "Sakar stood up."

    old "I'm going to head out for a small walk."
    new "I'm going to head out for a small walk."

    old "Care to join me?"
    new "Care to join me?"

    old "Join Sakar on his walk"
    new "Join Sakar on his walk"

    old "Sarah thought about it, then decided to join him."
    new "Sarah thought about it, then decided to join him."

    old "It was her and the others out here on the road. She needed to get to know the other men she was travelling with."
    new "It was her and the others out here on the road. She needed to get to know the other men she was travelling with."

    old "Sigmund had warned her about Sakar, but Sarah decided to make up her own mind about the man."
    new "Sigmund had warned her about Sakar, but Sarah decided to make up her own mind about the man."

    old "Yes, I'll join you."
    new "Yes, I'll join you."

    old "Sakar gestured out towards the woods."
    new "Sakar gestured out towards the woods."

    old "Not too far, we don't wanna get lost. But there is a nice spot not far from here."
    new "Not too far, we don't wanna get lost. But there is a nice spot not far from here."

    old "He began to walk, not waiting for her to catch up."
    new "He began to walk, not waiting for her to catch up."

    old "Sarah followed him as best she could."
    new "Sarah followed him as best she could."

    old "As Sakar ducked and weaved through the trees and the thick brush, Sarah tried to do the same."
    new "As Sakar ducked and weaved through the trees and the thick brush, Sarah tried to do the same."

    old "She quickly realized that the dress she was wearing was poorly suited for the forest."
    new "She quickly realized that the dress she was wearing was poorly suited for the forest."

    old "With each step, she could feel it catching on a twig or branch, slowing her down."
    new "With each step, she could feel it catching on a twig or branch, slowing her down."

    old "Still, she kept her pace, forcing her way through the forest."
    new "Still, she kept her pace, forcing her way through the forest."

    old "Being alone with Sakar was one thing, but being entirely alone in this forest somehow felt even more dangerous."
    new "Being alone with Sakar was one thing, but being entirely alone in this forest somehow felt even more dangerous."

    old "Pushing through, Sarah finally broke through a last cover of brush, and suddenly found the space around her open up as she stepped into a clearing."
    new "Pushing through, Sarah finally broke through a last cover of brush, and suddenly found the space around her open up as she stepped into a clearing."

    old "She found Sakar already there, sitting atop a boulder, looking at her."
    new "She found Sakar already there, sitting atop a boulder, looking at her."

    old "I thought I'd lost you there for a second."
    new "I thought I'd lost you there for a second."

    old "You almost did."
    new "You almost did."

    old "Sarah spun around, looking at the nature around her."
    new "Sarah spun around, looking at the nature around her."

    old "The clearing was covered with bright flowers that didn't seem to bloom anywhere else."
    new "The clearing was covered with bright flowers that didn't seem to bloom anywhere else."

    old "She had truly never seen anything like the raw nature of this place."
    new "She had truly never seen anything like the raw nature of this place."

    old "It's beautiful..."
    new "It's beautiful..."

    old "I thought you'd like it."
    new "I thought you'd like it."

    old "I tried to show the others last time we passed by here, but I don't think they're much for appreciating nature."
    new "I tried to show the others last time we passed by here, but I don't think they're much for appreciating nature."

    old "Sarah concluded that he was probably right about that."
    new "Sarah concluded that he was probably right about that."

    old "How did you find it?"
    new "How did you find it?"

    old "Luck I suppose."
    new "Luck I suppose."

    old "They're fine people, but I can't be around them for too long, so I like to wander away from the camp."
    new "They're fine people, but I can't be around them for too long, so I like to wander away from the camp."

    old "That's when I happened to find this place."
    new "That's when I happened to find this place."

    old "I don't think any other human in the world ever came here, besides me."
    new "I don't think any other human in the world ever came here, besides me."

    old "And now you too, I suppose."
    new "And now you too, I suppose."

    old "Thank you for showing me this."
    new "Thank you for showing me this."

    old "I just thought, after what you've seen today, you might like the distraction."
    new "I just thought, after what you've seen today, you might like the distraction."

    old "Sarah looked at the flowers."
    new "Sarah looked at the flowers."

    old "You mean those two men?"
    new "You mean those two men?"

    old "Yeah. Couldn't have been easy to see that."
    new "Yeah. Couldn't have been easy to see that."

    old "I can handle it. Just got to get tougher, I guess."
    new "I can handle it. Just got to get tougher, I guess."

    old "Maybe you can stand to get a bit tougher, Sarah, but don't let that bastard Sigmund grind you down."
    new "Maybe you can stand to get a bit tougher, Sarah, but don't let that bastard Sigmund grind you down."

    old "It's not a weakness to be shocked at the sight of blood. It reminds you that you're human, even if spilling it is sometimes necessary."
    new "It's not a weakness to be shocked at the sight of blood. It reminds you that you're human, even if spilling it is sometimes necessary."

    old "Sarah didn't know what to say, and so chose to say nothing."
    new "Sarah didn't know what to say, and so chose to say nothing."

    old "Slowly walking around the clearing, she explored ever inch of the nature that was so alien to her. Nothing like this existed in Rosanna."
    new "Slowly walking around the clearing, she explored ever inch of the nature that was so alien to her. Nothing like this existed in Rosanna."

